==English==
===Etymology===
From the Latin ''dedicatio'', from ''dedicare'', ''to proclaim''.

===Noun===
'''dedication'''

#The act of dedicating, the state of being dedicated.
#A note addressed to a patron or friend, prefixed to a work of art, as a token of respect, esteem, or affestion.
#Selfless devotion to a cause.
#: "''George Washington served America with dedication.''"
#The rite of setting apart or consecrating a thing or place.
#:"''the dedication of Solomon's temple.''"
#A devoting or setting aside for a particular purpose.
#:"''the lands were dedicated for public use.''"

